CSS Day 2: Text Styling, Fonts & Colors

Today you'll learn how to make text look professional.

Topics

✅ Colors
✅ Font Size
✅ Font Family
✅ Font Weight
✅ Text Alignment
✅ Text Decoration
✅ Line Height

1. Text Color

Change text color using color.

h1 {
    color: blue;
}

p {
    color: green;
}

You can use:

color: red;
color: #ff0000;
color: rgb(255, 0, 0);
2. Background Color
body {
    background-color: lightgray;
}
h1 {
    background-color: yellow;
}
3. Font Size
h1 {
    font-size: 36px;
}

p {
    font-size: 18px;
}

Common sizes:

16px → normal text
24px → subheading
32px+ → heading
4. Font Family

Changes the text style.

body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

Examples:

font-family: Arial;
font-family: Verdana;
font-family: Times New Roman;
font-family: sans-serif;
5. Font Weight

Controls boldness.

h1 {
    font-weight: bold;
}

Values:

font-weight: normal;
font-weight: bold;
font-weight: 100;
font-weight: 400;
font-weight: 700;
6. Text Alignment
h1 {
    text-align: center;
}

Options:

text-align: left;
text-align: center;
text-align: right;
7. Text Decoration

Remove or add underlines.

a {
    text-decoration: none;
}

Examples:

text-decoration: underline;
text-decoration: none;
text-decoration: line-through;
8. Line Height

Controls spacing between lines.

p {
    line-height: 1.8;
}

Without line-height:

Text looks crowded

With line-height:

Text becomes easier to read


Interview Questions
1. Difference between color and background-color?

Answer:

color changes text color.
background-color changes the background color.
2. What is font-family?

Answer:

It specifies the font style used to display text.

3. What is font-weight?

Answer:

It controls the thickness or boldness of text.

4. What does text-align: center do?

Answer:

It aligns text horizontally in the center.

5. Why use line-height?

Answer:

It improves readability by increasing space between lines.
